  "texts": [
    "The pooling operation effectively addresses the challenges of nonlinearity and spatial and temporal correlation in the precipitation process by mapping the neighboring features to the feature space with the same dimension as the central node, which provides strong technical support for weather forecasting and disaster warning.",
    "In the field of cybersecurity, graph pooling techniques are widely used to deal with a variety of security problems, such as anomaly detection, Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attack detection, malware detection, and vulnerability detection in source code.",
    "In the field of cybersecurity anomaly detection, (Abou Rida et al. 2021) adopted an inductive graph neural network to detect anomalies.",
    "This approach utilizes two different aggregation strategies: GraphSAGE-Mean and GraphSAGE-Pool.",
    "GraphSAGE-Mean uses the average of neighboring nodes' features to perform aggregation, while GraphSAGE-Pool first processes the features of neighboring nodes through a fully-connected layer, and subsequently applies a maximum pooling operation."
